      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "x = np.arange(0,100)\n",
        "y = x*2\n",
        "z = x**2"

      },

      },
      "source": [
        "## Exercise 1\n",
        "\n",
        "**Follow along with these steps**\n",
        "* Create a figure object called fig using plt.figure()\n",
        "* Use add_axes to add an axis to the figure canvas at [0,0,1,1]. Call this new axis ax.\n",
        "* Plot (x,y) on that axes and set the labels and titles to match the plot below:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "03Ts4r5SST2g",
        "outputId": "52a5e922-cefc-413b-99e3-2cba506a6792",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 582
        }
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "fig=plt.figure()\n",
        "ax=fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",
        "\n",
        "ax.plot(x,y)\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"x\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"y\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"title\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },

      "source": [

        "**Create a figure object and put two axes on it, ax1 and ax2. Located at [0,0,1,1] and [0.2,0.5,.2,.2] respectively.**"

      "cell_type": "code",

              "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "fig=plt.figure()\n",
        "ax1=fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",

      "source": [
        "fig=plt.figure()\n",

        "ax1=fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",
        "ax2=fig.add_axes([0.2,0.5,.4,.4])\n",
        "ax1.plot(x,z,'b')\n",
        "ax1.set_xlabel('X')\n",

        "ax2.plot(x,y,'b')\n",
        "ax2.set_xlabel('X')\n",
        "ax2.set_ylabel('Y')\n",
        "ax2.set_title('zoom')\n",
        "ax2.set_xlim([20,22])\n",

        "plt.show()"

        "\n",
        "**Use plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2) to create the plot below.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QWwItNZVST2r"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Now plot (x,y) and (x,z) on the axes. Play around with the linewidth and style**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2)\n",
        "axes[0].plot([0,100],[0,200],ls=':',color='blue')\n",
        "axes[1].plot([0,100],[0,10000],color='red')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.show()"
